{
  "stem": "12447.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So he would take care of the locks and the windows, and all that.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we were able to buy food and eat from that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So that continued through the winter.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they continued pretty normal, as far as I'm-- I remember, until it got in into the summer of 1940.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Except that it was very dangerous for my father to walk in the streets.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Every once in awhile, the Germans would beat up Jewish men, especially older people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Germans, by themselves, did not identify the Jews that were not visual as Jews-- they did not look like Jews.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If any Jew wore a, a Jewish hat-- which they used to wear a black hat with a beard-- they would identify them as Jews.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But if a Jew did not wear that, they couldn't identify the Jew directly.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But the danger came in that every once in awhile, they would catch men to work.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And for some reason, the Polacks would help out the Germans catch these men.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They would identify the Jewish men walking the street.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My father had a hook nose, didn't speak Polish very well-- he spoke Polish well, but he had a Jewish accent.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So did my mother.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "If you conversed with my father probably like two sentences, you could have told-- you could identify him that he was a Jew.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I don't remember exactly at what point they came up with the-- with the [NON-ENGLISH], what they called it, that you had to wear the Jewish-- the Star of David, which was, in Warsaw, a white band with a blue [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] sign of David, the Magen David.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So-- but I, I don't remember at what month they came out with this law that you had to wear it.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
